    "updated_at": "2014-12-22T00:59:41Z",
    "body": "Can we add a lint or something for \"probably wrong\" implementations of `Sync` or `Send` (i.e. implementations for types that wouldn't be `Sync` or `Send` today)? I'm a bit worried with the current setup that it'll be really easy to accidentally mess up and turn a previously safe object into an unsafe object by adding something that's not `Sync` or `Send`.\n\nI'm also not really sure why `RacyCell` exists, unless we add that lint.\n",
