    "created_at": "2014-12-28T09:14:26Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-12-28T09:14:26Z",
    "body": "@shadowmint note that it's not always required a `Send + Sync` bound on every implementation of `Send`. The bounds will depend on the type your implementing `Send`/`Sync` for.\n\nAs for the broken `*` pointers, there's a [`Unique`](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/7df17a2868004597bff61348060f423ad2384e04/src/libcore/ptr.rs#L506-L536) struct that you can use to wrap them. `Unique` _owns_ the reference to the wrapped value, therefore it's `Send` and `Sync`. \n\nFor example:\n\n``` rust\nextern crate core;\nextern crate libc;\n\nuse libc::c_int;\nuse core::ptr::Unique;\n\nfn test_send<T:Send>(s: T) {}\n\nfn main() {\n\n    let x = Unique(0 as *mut libc::c_int);\n    test_send(x);\n    // test_send(0 as *mut libc::c_int); // this fails\n}\n```\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
